Abstract. This project presents SeniorCare, an IoT-based system designed to
continuously monitor elderly people. The solution integrates a simulated sensor platform in ESP32, a cloud backend for data processing, and a real-time
dashboard for family monitoring. The IoT module is fully implemented in the
Wokwi simulation environment, allowing for a faithful reproduction of the circuit, sensors, and reading logic without the need for physical hardware. The
system monitors temperature, decreased oxygen saturation, falls, and routine
check-ins. The architecture uses MQTT for communication and Firebase for
storage.
